noun.description: The seventh letter of the Greek alphabet (Η, η), transliterated as e or ē.

proper noun.description: A Basque separatist movement in Spain, founded in 1959.

abbreviation.description: Edited to add (used in online discussions to indicate that one has modified the content of a post one has made, typically in order to add something)
examples: ETA: sorry, didn't see your post before I posted mine, @Abc!

origin: Basque acronym, from Euzkadi ta Azkatasuna Basque homeland and liberty.
